---
description: Dockerized infrastructure conventions for infra/ (Postgres, pgAdmin, Authentik).
globs: infra/**
---

`infra/` holds docker-compose stacks, driven via Nx `up`/`down`/`logs` targets (`nx:run-commands` wrapping `docker compose`).

- `infra/timemanager-db` — Postgres 15 (`:5432`, db `timemanager`, user `postgres`) + pgAdmin (`:8080`). Volumes live under `./data/` (gitignored). Start with `pnpm db:up` / `nx run timemanager-db:up`.
- `infra/authentik` — Authentik auth stack; independent from the DB stack. Keep `.env` gitignored and `.env.example` in sync (`PG_PASS`, `AUTHENTIK_SECRET_KEY`). Compose expects `media/`, `certs/`, `custom-templates/` dirs.

Rules:

- Never commit `.env` files or `data/` volume contents.
- Do not migrate existing volume data between machines; a fresh local DB re-seeded via `nx run timemanager-api:seed` is the expected workflow.
